snippet: David Bird, 55, was last seen Saturday when he told his wife that he planned to go on a walk through the wooded trails near their home in New Jersey.
abstract: Hundreds of law enforcement officers and volunteers search swampy woodland in central New Jersey in search of Wall Street Journal reporter David Bird, who went for weekend walk through wooded trails near his Long Hill Township home and never returned.

byline.original: By NATE SCHWEBER and MICHAEL SCHWIRTZ
byline.contributor: Nate Schweber reported from Long Hill Township, and Michael Schwirtz from New York.

lead_paragraph: David Bird, 55, was last seen Saturday when he told his wife that he planned to go on a walk through the wooded trails near their home in New Jersey.

headline.main: Authorities Comb New Jersey Woodland in Hunt for Missing Reporter
headline.print_headline: Authorities Comb New Jersey Woodland in Hunt for Missing Reporter
